title: November 29 (Eastern Orthodox liturgics)
text:
<a href="November%2028%20%28Eastern%20Orthodox%20liturgics%29">November 28</a> - <a href="Eastern%20Orthodox%20liturgical%20calendar">Eastern Orthodox liturgical calendar</a> - <a href="November%2030%20%28Eastern%20Orthodox%20liturgics%29">November 30</a>
All fixed commemorations below are observed on December 12 by <a href="Eastern%20Orthodox%20Church">Eastern Orthodox Church</a>es on the <a href="Julian%20Calendar">Old Calendar</a>.
For November 29, Orthodox Churches on the Old Calendar commemorate the Saints listed on <a href="November%2016%20%28Eastern%20Orthodox%20liturgics%29">November 16</a>.
